# Spring Boot Service Layer Patterns

## 📌 PURPOSE

Service layer contains business logic.

---

## 🧱 STRUCTURE

### DO

* Use `@Service`
* Keep logic independent of controller

### EXAMPLE

```java
@Service
public class TaskService {
}
```

---

## ⚙️ RESPONSIBILITIES

### DO

* Handle business logic
* Validate business rules
* Call repository
* Map DTO ↔ Entity

---

## 🔄 DTO MAPPING

### DO

* Convert Request DTO → Entity
* Convert Entity → Response DTO

---

## ❗ EXCEPTION HANDLING

### DO

* Throw exceptions for:

  * Not found
  * Invalid state

### DO NOT

* Do not swallow exceptions

---

## 🧾 BUSINESS RULES

### DO

* Validate domain rules

### EXAMPLE

```java
if (task == null) {
    throw new ResourceNotFoundException("Task not found");
}
```

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* No HTTP logic
* No annotations like @RequestMapping
* No direct request handling

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep methods small
* Use meaningful names
* Follow single responsibility

---

## 🧪 TDD RULES

### DO

* Write unit tests for service
* Cover edge cases

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST contain business logic
* MUST call repository
* MUST throw exceptions
* MUST NOT depend on controller

---

